{
  "stem": "20142.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Dzielna ?] Street, from the Karmelizka Street, who-- I met [INAUDIBLE] in 1940, and he encouraged me to join the Hashomer Hatzair organization in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they-- how I contacted-- through him, I contacted the outside war, outside of ghetto, organization of PPS.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "PPS is the Polish Party of-- Socialist Party.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I volunteered to conduct for them services of distributing illegal newspapers to some of the people, known only to the PPS, and-- who wanted to receive news directly printed by the organization.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they listened to the BBC, British Broadcasting Corporation.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And their news were printed night, at night, and delivered during the day or the following day.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "According to the habits of the people living outside of the ghetto, they knew that they had to be very careful because they were always followed by somebody.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we learned the tricks of finding out if anybody is followed or watched by the agent of Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I did realize that Germany status has to be undermined.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And people have to learn how-- what news are coming from the outside world to spread among the population by mouth.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So chosen people were getting newsletters from the party for the benefit of the other people who were gathering or meeting together.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Meetings, when I mean meetings, is contact of good friends who occasionally met in coffeehouse or met on the street, walk for some time.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then they were not allowed any meetings, official meetings of any parties or anything unless they were pro-Nazis and they had the approval of the German authority.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "PPS?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "PPS?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No, they were strictly Polish party.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
